    opt.map(|x| x * 2)
}

let doubled = double_option(Some(5));
```
In this snippet, `double_option` is a pure function that transforms the inner value of an Option, assuming it contains some data. If you don’t know whether your Option has a value (as in Rust), `.map()` allows safe transformation without panicking.

